# Pre-Researcher — KS Global Estates

## A — Client Brand Assets

- **KS Global Estates live site:** `https://ksglobalestates.com` and `https://www.ksglobalestates.com` both return HTTP 403. Site may exist behind Cloudflare/bot protection or may not yet be live. Either way, no brand assets extractable.
- **Verdict:** No brand colors, logo, or typography available. Planner should invent a credible luxury identity from scratch.
- No LinkedIn/Instagram found with a quick lookup (name too generic to resolve without site anchor).

## B — Luxury Real Estate Design Conventions

**Layout:**
- Premium RE sites (Sotheby's International Realty, Knight Frank, Compass, Christie's, JLL) use editorial asymmetric layouts, NOT centered hero + symmetrical sections.
- Full-bleed imagery dominates: hero at 100vh, property cards 16:9 with overlay text. Thin horizontal rules replace heavy card borders.
- Generous negative space; content rarely fills more than ~65-70% of the viewport width on desktop.
- "Story" pages interleave large photography with tight editorial columns (40/60 or 30/70 splits).
- Scroll-triggered reveals are common but subtle (opacity + translateY, not spin/bounce).

**Typography (dominant patterns in the sector):**
- Serif headline + humanist/geometric sans body: `Cormorant Garamond` / `Playfair Display` paired with `DM Sans`, `Neue Montreal`, or `Graphik`.
- Weight contrast is extreme: headline at 300–400, label caps at 600–700.
- Tracked-out uppercase labels (`letter-spacing: 0.2em`) for category tags and nav items are a signature luxury tell.
- Body text 15–16px, line-height ~1.7. Comfortable; never cramped.

**Palette (luxury RE conventions):**
- Deep charcoal (`#1A1A1A` / `#0D0D0D`) backgrounds for hero/dark sections.
- Warm off-white (`#F8F5F0` / `#FAF8F4`) for light sections — never pure white.
- Single luxury accent: muted gold (`#B8975A` / `#C9A96E`) or warm bronze used sparingly on CTAs, borders, dividers.
- Suggested bespoke palette for KS Global Estates:
  - `--ink: #12100E` (near-black, warm)
  - `--canvas: #F5F1EB` (warm parchment)
  - `--gold: #B8975A` (muted antique gold)
  - `--mid: #6B6560` (warm gray, secondary text)
  - `--surface: #FFFFFF`
  - `--dark-section: #1C1917` (dark warm sections)

**Motion (premium vs. cheap):**
- Premium: slow fade-up (0.6s ease-out), parallax hero image, subtle price-pin drop on map load.
- Cheap: bouncing loaders, CSS pulse animations on text, infinite scroll carousels with visible arrows.

**Map + list UX (Zillow/Redfin/Compass patterns):**
- Split-pane is the industry norm: ~55% map / ~45% list, resizable.
- Hovering a list card highlights the corresponding map pin (color change + scale); clicking opens detail.
- Price labels directly on map pins are the standard differentiator vs. generic circle markers.
- Filter panel docks above the list column (sticky), NOT a full-screen modal on desktop.

## C — AI Tell-Tale Checklist (patterns to EXCLUDE)

**Layout tells:**
- Centered hero with H1 + subtitle + CTA button, then 3 equally spaced icon cards below.
- "Features" section with icon-left + text-right repeated rows.
- Blob/wave SVG section dividers (especially purple-to-indigo gradient blobs).
- "Testimonials" section with round avatar + star rating + quote in a 3-col card row.
- Footer with 4 equal-width columns, each with a "Quick Links" heading.
- Sticky hero with text centered over a stock photo at full opacity (no overlay treatment).

**Color/gradient tells:**
- Purple-to-indigo (`#6366F1` to `#8B5CF6`) gradient on any element.
- Teal + coral duotone CTAs.
- `border-radius: 9999px` on every button.
- Box-shadow `0 4px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.1)` on every card (identical, AI default).
- Pure `#FFFFFF` background with pure `#000000` text (zero warmth).

**Typography tells:**
- `font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif` as the ONLY font.
- `font-family: 'Outfit'` or `'Nunito'` at `font-weight: 400` for ALL text.
- H1-H6 on a locked modular scale (e.g., exactly 48/36/24/20/16/14) with no size deviation.
- Uppercase "FEATURES" / "SERVICES" / "ABOUT US" nav items with `font-weight: 700`.

**Card / component tells:**
- Uniform 3-column grid of rounded cards with identical height and padding.
- Animated counters (`0 → 500+`) in a "Stats" section.
- Frosted glass (`backdrop-filter: blur`) on every overlay regardless of context.
- Thin colored left-border accent cards (frequently used for "facts" sections).

**Copy / content tells:**
- "Unlock your potential" / "Empowering your journey" / "We are committed to excellence" hero headers.
- Fake testimonials with generated avatars (Unsplash face photos + star ratings).
- "Our Process" section with Step 1 / Step 2 / Step 3 in a horizontal timeline.
- "Trusted by 500+ clients" stat without any proof.

**What reads as HUMAN-CRAFTED instead:**
- Asymmetric column grids (e.g., 7/5, 8/4) that break the equal-halves convention.
- Oversized display type that deliberately overflows or clips — editorial risk-taking.
- Mixed type scales: one heading at 96px while body stays 15px (extreme contrast, intentional).
- A dominant photographic moment occupying 80-100% of the viewport with type treatment as art direction, not overlay.
- Textural detail: thin 1px gold borders, letter-spaced micro-labels, deliberate grid rule lines.
- Opinionated whitespace that leaves sections intentionally sparse, trusting the imagery.
- Horizontal scrolling feature for property gallery (rare enough to feel crafted).
- Map pins with price labels styled to match the site's design system (not Leaflet defaults).

